title: nightly: ICE: borrow checker panic instead of error on borrow of moved value

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust pub struct DataStruct(); pub struct HelperStruct<'n> { pub helpers: [Vec<&'n i64>; 2], pub is_empty: bool, } impl DataStruct { pub fn f(&self) -> HelperStruct { let helpers = [vec![], vec![]]; HelperStruct { helpers, is_empty: helpers[0].is_empty() } // borrow of moved value } } ``` ### Meta Playground beta `1.60.0-beta.2` correctly reports: ``` error[E0382]: borrow of moved value: `helpers` --> src/lib.rs:13:43 ``` But Playground nightly `rustc 1.61.0-nightly (c274e4969 2022-03-05)` instead ICE's ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'index out of bounds: the len is 0 but the index is 13', compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/region_constraints/mod.rs:446:9 ... query stack during panic: #0 [mir_borrowck] borrow-checking `::f` #1 [analysis] running analysis passes on this crate ```
